1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
As we have learned, blocks form the cornerstone of building your online home.

2
00:00:04,560 --> 00:00:07,560
You can think of them as the literal building blocks of your website.

3
00:00:08,160 --> 00:00:11,160
In this lesson, we are going to build on our knowledge of blocks.

4
00:00:11,640 --> 00:00:14,640
Explore using various types of blocks,

5
00:00:14,200 --> 00:00:17,200
as well as nest and group blocks together to create various layouts.

6
00:00:18,240 --> 00:00:21,240
Nested blocks help you create more complex layouts by adding multiple blocks inside each other.

7
00:00:24,240 --> 00:00:27,240
We typically use container blocks such as the Group block, Columns block, Cover block,

8
00:00:29,240 --> 00:00:32,240
the Media and Text block or Row block to group content together.

9
00:00:33,560 --> 00:00:36,560
As a reminder, when you open up the List View,

10
00:00:36,480 --> 00:00:39,480
you can navigate between layers of content and nested blocks.

11
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:44,000
Let's look at the second section on this homepage to see this in action.

12
00:00:45,520 --> 00:00:48,520
So I'll go ahead and select the Columns block.

13
00:00:49,080 --> 00:00:52,080
And when we expand the Columns block, we will see all the blocks inside.

14
00:00:55,680 --> 00:00:58,680
In the left column, we will notice a Heading block, a Separator block and a Paragraph block.

15
00:01:04,560 --> 00:01:07,560
And in the right column, we will see a Gallery block with four different images.

16
00:01:11,560 --> 00:01:14,560
Let's go ahead and create some examples together.

17
00:01:14,320 --> 00:01:17,320
Firstly, I'm going to group some blocks together using a Group block.

18
00:01:18,600 --> 00:01:21,600
But first, I'm going to add a Heading block.

19
00:01:24,440 --> 00:01:27,440
And then name it appropriately.

20
00:01:26,360 --> 00:01:29,360
In this case, laughter is the best medicine.

21
00:01:31,560 --> 00:01:34,560
Then I'll press Enter and add a Columns block.

22
00:01:37,800 --> 00:01:40,800
And select two equal columns.

23
00:01:41,600 --> 00:01:44,600
And then add some text in the left column.

24
00:01:46,080 --> 00:01:49,080
And in the right column.

25
00:01:50,040 --> 00:01:53,040
Then I will select both of these blocks in my list view by holding in shift and clicking

26
00:01:55,920 --> 00:01:58,920
on my mouse, which allows you to select multiple blocks and then use the block toolbar to

27
00:02:02,040 --> 00:02:05,040
group them together in a Group block.

28
00:02:06,800 --> 00:02:09,800
Next, I would like to change the width of the Group block to wide width.

29
00:02:11,080 --> 00:02:14,080
But before I will be able to do that, I have to deselect Inner blocks use content width.

30
00:02:17,800 --> 00:02:20,800
Only once I've deselected this option, the nested blocks will be able to use the content

31
00:02:23,360 --> 00:02:26,360
width options, such as wide width and full width.

32
00:02:27,520 --> 00:02:30,520
If I don't deselect this option, I won't be able to change the alignment to full width,

33
00:02:33,360 --> 00:02:36,360
for example.

34
00:02:35,160 --> 00:02:38,160
As you can see, nothing happens.

35
00:02:38,600 --> 00:02:41,600
So once deselected, I can return to the block toolbar and change the width to wide width

36
00:02:44,680 --> 00:02:47,680
without the constraints set by the theme.

37
00:02:47,040 --> 00:02:50,040
Next, we can open up the Styles tab to style our block further.

38
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:54,000
The first thing I want to do is change the background color of the Group block.

39
00:02:55,960 --> 00:02:58,960
And then please also note, you can add a background image to a Group block if you wanted to.

40
00:03:01,840 --> 00:03:04,840
And click on the three vertical dots next to Typography to see all the options available.

41
00:03:08,120 --> 00:03:11,120
Next, I will go ahead and add some padding to create more space around the content of

42
00:03:13,920 --> 00:03:16,920
my block.

43
00:03:14,480 --> 00:03:17,480
And there you have it.

44
00:03:19,240 --> 00:03:22,240
And of course, you may decide to style your Group block even further.

45
00:03:24,800 --> 00:03:27,800
When you have multiple layers of content on a page, you can use the Group block to rename

46
00:03:30,560 --> 00:03:33,560
sections.

47
00:03:31,560 --> 00:03:34,560
So, in the top example, we will see the first section is called Our story and now I can select

48
00:03:37,920 --> 00:03:40,920
the Group block below and rename it.

49
00:03:41,040 --> 00:03:44,040
In this case, Testimonial.

50
00:03:45,160 --> 00:03:48,160
So this feature of the Group block will allow you to structure and organize your content.

51
00:03:52,040 --> 00:03:55,040
In the next example, let's use the Media and Text block to group blocks together.

52
00:03:57,320 --> 00:04:00,320
So let's go ahead and add the Media and Text block.

53
00:04:01,040 --> 00:04:04,040
And then on the left, we can add an image from our media library.

54
00:04:08,320 --> 00:04:11,320
And on the right, we can start adding content.

55
00:04:11,560 --> 00:04:14,560
At the top, I will add a heading and name it Sushi is art.

56
00:04:19,360 --> 00:04:22,360
Press enter and then add some text.

57
00:04:22,760 --> 00:04:25,760
At the bottom, I want to add a call to action or in this case, a Buttons block.

58
00:04:30,320 --> 00:04:33,320
And then I'll say Learn more.

59
00:04:33,920 --> 00:04:36,920
And I'll use the block toolbar to make the text bold and also to add the relevant URL.

60
00:04:42,120 --> 00:04:45,120
Then I will select the parent block in the List View and change the alignment to wide

61
00:04:48,320 --> 00:04:51,320
width.

62
00:04:50,680 --> 00:04:53,680
You can also use the block toolbar if you wanted to change and show the image on the

63
00:04:55,800 --> 00:04:58,800
right.

64
00:04:57,640 --> 00:05:00,640
And then below Settings, I will change the media width to 40.

65
00:05:06,280 --> 00:05:09,280
Then I will open up the Styles tab and add some padding around the content.

66
00:05:13,640 --> 00:05:16,640
And then finally, I will change the vertical alignment of the image to align bottom.

67
00:05:23,040 --> 00:05:26,040
And that's it.

68
00:05:25,240 --> 00:05:28,240
Our Media and Text block is done.

69
00:05:28,440 --> 00:05:31,440
In the next example, we are going to use the Columns block.

70
00:05:31,440 --> 00:05:34,440
The Columns block is one of the most effective blocks to use to create complex layouts or

71
00:05:35,560 --> 00:05:38,560
various designs.

72
00:05:37,040 --> 00:05:40,040
So let's go ahead and add a Columns block and then select three equal columns.

73
00:05:44,440 --> 00:05:47,440
And then in the left column, I'm going to go ahead and add some text and name it Platters,

74
00:05:52,520 --> 00:05:55,520
press enter and then add a paragraph.

75
00:05:57,120 --> 00:06:00,120
Below that, I'm going to add an Image block and select an image from my media library.

76
00:06:08,440 --> 00:06:11,440
Then I will select the text at the top, make it bold and also enlarge the size followed

77
00:06:16,960 --> 00:06:19,960
by centering the text of both paragraphs.

78
00:06:22,880 --> 00:06:25,880
And once it's aligned center, I will select the Image block and change the aspect ratio

79
00:06:28,080 --> 00:06:31,080
to square.

80
00:06:32,040 --> 00:06:35,040
Then I will select the main Columns block or the parent block and change the alignment

81
00:06:37,320 --> 00:06:40,320
to wide width.

82
00:06:39,840 --> 00:06:42,840
Then I will make my way to Styles and add some padding around the content of the block,

83
00:06:47,080 --> 00:06:50,080
as well as block spacing between the three columns.

84
00:06:53,560 --> 00:06:56,560
When I'm done with styling the block, I'm going to select the left column and duplicate

85
00:06:59,760 --> 00:07:02,760
it twice.

86
00:07:05,400 --> 00:07:08,400
And once duplicated, we can delete the empty columns.

87
00:07:13,600 --> 00:07:16,600
And then we can go ahead and modify the content as we please.

88
00:07:20,360 --> 00:07:23,360
In the last example, we are going to use a Cover block.

89
00:07:23,640 --> 00:07:26,640
The Cover block allows you to display text and other content on top of an image or video.

90
00:07:28,760 --> 00:07:31,760
It is a great block to use for headers and banner style displays.

91
00:07:32,840 --> 00:07:35,840
So let's go ahead and add our Cover block.

92
00:07:36,120 --> 00:07:39,120
Then you will see that you can select a color overlay.

93
00:07:41,480 --> 00:07:44,480
But I'm going to go ahead and add an image from my media library as background.

94
00:07:47,920 --> 00:07:50,920
Then I will add some text followed by a Buttons block.

95
00:07:56,880 --> 00:07:59,880
Then I will write Order now and then change the background color and the text color of

96
00:08:03,880 --> 00:08:06,880
my call to action.

97
00:08:11,400 --> 00:08:14,400
Then I will select both of the blocks and stack them together using a Stack block.

98
00:08:19,400 --> 00:08:22,400
This allows me to customize the blocks simultaneously.

99
00:08:23,160 --> 00:08:26,160
Then I will justify the Stack block to center, select the Cover block and change the alignment

100
00:08:32,120 --> 00:08:35,120
to wide width.

101
00:08:34,600 --> 00:08:37,600
And don't forget to deselect Inner blocks use content width.

102
00:08:39,800 --> 00:08:42,800
Now we can make further modifications.

103
00:08:42,120 --> 00:08:45,120
I will enlarge the text, enjoy 20% off as well as the Buttons block.

104
00:08:53,120 --> 00:08:56,120
I also want to make the text of the Buttons block bold and don't forget to add your URL.

105
00:09:03,880 --> 00:09:06,880
Then I will select the Cover block and please note in the block toolbar you have the option

106
00:09:09,160 --> 00:09:12,160
to toggle the block to full height.

107
00:09:12,720 --> 00:09:15,720
But then we can also manually decrease or increase the size.

108
00:09:19,720 --> 00:09:22,720
Then I will open up the Styles tab and change the overlay opacity to 30 to make it lighter.

109
00:09:30,440 --> 00:09:33,440
And then my cover block is ready to go.

110
00:09:35,480 --> 00:09:38,480
I trust you now feel more confident nesting and grouping blocks together.

